main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Burlington, Massachusetts on July 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as luminous and moved behind a cloud for 10 to 15 seconds., Insufficient data was available for evaluation and the form was sent back for additional information., The object was reported to have a bright glow and appeared oval or circular in shape., The object made no sound and was under observation for approximately 15 minutes., The investigation was led by DST Dan H. Manning, USAF.
sighted object: a luminous oval or circular object
